programme.title: Wildest India: The Himalayas: Surviving the Summits
programme.desc: The Himalayas run across 2,500km of north India. he Himalayas' rugged highlands offer little direct refuge to humans, in the shadow below, over a billion people in India rely on the mountains for survival.

programme.title: Wildest India: India's Lost World
programme.desc: North-east India is an anthropological paradise; there is no other place on Earth with so many different ethnic groups. The forest are filled with mysterious tribes whose lives are dictated by the rain and the seasonal fruits of the forest.

programme.title: Wildest India: Western Ghats: Monsoon Mountains
programme.desc: See how the Himalayas run across 2,500km of north India.The Himalayas' highlands offer little direct refuge to humans. /Then, learn about the western Ghats. A spine of mountains that lay claim to being one of the most bio-diverse places in the world.

programme.title: Wildest India: Thar Desert: Sacred Sands
programme.desc: Covering 200,000 km sq, India's Thar desert is one of the harshest places on Earth. Desiccating winds and near permanent drought has earned this unforgiving land another name: the region of death.

programme.title: Wildest India: Ganges: River of Life
programme.desc: Then watch, the longest river in India, The Ganges. It's a lifeline to wild animals, from rhinoceros and river dolphins to otters and gharials.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado
programme.desc: Venezuela is famous for its lost worlds, its forbidding mountains, huge swamps, and impenetrable jungles, all seemingly cut off in space and time. Yet each is linked, by the mighty river: the Orinoco, the rumoured route to El Dorado, city of gold.
programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Pantanal: Brazil's Wild Heart

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth
programme.desc: Patagonia is a place of extremes  of vast ice fields and snow-capped mountains; of windswept deserts, and violent oceans. Survival here means being tough enough to cope with brutal winters, and canny enough to exploit brief seasons of plenty.
programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire
programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Devil's Due
programme.desc: During WWII, Greek Prime Ministers Tsolakoglou, Logothetopoulos, and Rallis collaborated with Nazi occupiers, imposing fees that caused a famine.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Croatian Collaborator
programme.desc: Croatia grapples with its fascist past through figures like Dinko Sakic, once hailed as a hero but later convicted of war crimes. Leading the notorious Jasenovac camp, Sakic oversaw brutal atrocities against inmates.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Belgian Collaborator
programme.desc: Leon Degrelle, a charismatic Belgian leader, joined the Nazis and led Die Wallonien on the Eastern Front. Despite no military background, he earned the Knight's Cross for valor. He recruited 4000 more for the SS, defending Berlin until April 1945.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Traitor-in-Chief
programme.desc: Pierre Laval, once celebrated and later reviled, faced execution in 1945 for collaboration with the Nazis during Vichy France. Originally a socialist and pacifist, he fell into collaboration for power and to navigate the horrors of occupation.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Hitler's Inside Man
programme.desc: Chaim Rumkowski, leader of the Lodz ghetto during WWII, believed cooperation with the Nazis could save lives, providing labor in exchange for food. This approach kept some semblance of community and culture alive amidst unimaginable horror.

programme.title: Hitler's Last Secrets: Fatal Liaison - The Strange Affair of Adolf and Eva
programme.desc: The protracted romance between Adolf Hitler and Eva Braun began in 1929 and ended in 1945 in the bunker under the ruins of the Chancellery.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The fourth episode sees the Germans well and truly on the retreat and the Allies are able to successfully implement operation Husky: the landing on Sicily.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The third episode opens with Rommel’s second offensive in North Africa.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The second episode starts on the morning of the 22nd of June 1941 when the Germans launched operation Barbarossa, the code name for the invasion of the Soviet Union.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: This first part of the series introduces the first tanks being deployed on the battlefields in northern France during WWI and describes the devastating effect these steel monsters had on an infantry confronted with them for the very first time.

programme.title: Gestapo: Hitler's Secret Police
programme.desc: Hermann Goering’s Secret State Police were tasked to arrest and torture confessions and information from supposed enemies of the Reich.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 2
programme.desc: This second episode covers the last week of March to late April. The cameramen covered many stories of victory and defeat, death and liberation. Faces of despair and joy, scenes of war and peace.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 1
programme.desc: This first episode covers the last week of February to late March. When American troops started their final invasion of Nazi Germany in February 1945, U.S. Army cameramen were at their side.

programme.title: Destroy Paris: Hitler's Secret Plan
programme.desc: By 1944, as the Reich was crumbling, Hitler gave detailed orders for the destruction of Paris. He wanted the monuments and all the bridges mined and the city reduced to a 'pile of rubble'.

programme.title: Battle of Britain: The Race For Radar
programme.desc: On the brink of war the Germans mount a daring Zeppelin spy mission. Had the Luftwaffe spies discovered Britain’s greatest secret?'

programme.title: Battle for the Bulge
programme.desc: The Battle for the Bulge was the last major German offensive move on the Western Front during the Second World War.

programme.title: Rommel: The Soldier, The Son, and Hitler
programme.desc: Never a member of the Nazi party, Rommel detested blending politics and war. He would quickly discover that both were always in play under Hitler.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Josef Goebbels
programme.desc: Josef Goebbels: A unique documentary looking at the role of Goebbels, a man from Hitler's inner circle.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Julius Streicher
programme.desc: Julius Streicher: A look at the role of Julius Streicher in the Nazi regime. Streicher was responsible for much anti-Semitic propaganda

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Hermann Goering
programme.desc: Hermann Goering: Hermann Goering was the commander-in-chief of the Luftwaffe and Hitler's designated successor. This is his dark story.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Albert Speer
programme.desc: Albert Speer: The career of Albert Speer, Hitler's architect, is explored in this documentary of dark figures.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Rise of The Bomber
programme.desc: Rise of the Bomber: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: War Without Boundaries
programme.desc: War Without Boundaries: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The Means To Victory
programme.desc: The Means to Victory: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The World At War
programme.desc: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Mega Transports: Conveyance of the Norwegian Joy
programme.desc: Meyer Werft in Germany is one of the biggest shipbuilders in the world. But it's problem is as big as the ships it builds: the coast and sea are 50 kilometres away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Superyachts
programme.desc: Transporting a ship by a ship - this becomes necessary when the super-rich want their super yacht available on the other side of the world, but do not want to sail it there themselves.

programme.title: Mega Transports: AutoClav
programme.desc: A unique mega transport made of steel and titanium with a special purpose: to extract tons of gold. This so-called autoclave is the biggest of its kind. Its weight: over one thousand tons.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Villagemove
programme.desc: Everyone knows it: Housemoving is a lot of work, requires excellent planning and costs time and money. Just imagine how it must be if you are moving an entire village - as a whole.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Wind Park
programme.desc: A wind park needs to get from Europe to Asia. Over two thousand tons of highly sensitive and valuable cargo. On one of the world's largest heavy lift vessels.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Mining Truck
programme.desc: If a transporter needs to be transported, if 176 wheels aren't enough to carry its weight and if the load weighs twice as much as the transporter... Then it must be the mother of all mega transports!

programme.title: Mega Transports: Gigantic Autoliner
programme.desc: A transport to the other side of the globe. The Höegh Trapper is the largest automobile transporter in the world. Two hundred meters long, thirty-six meters wide.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Siberian Ice Road
programme.desc: A Mega Transport on one of the most dangerous roads in the world. The Siberian Ice Road. It doesn't forgive mistakes. It's treacherous. And unpredictable.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Antonov
programme.desc: A giant of the skies - the Antonov AN-124-100M-150. Worldwide the biggest production cargo aircraft of all time. No aircraft can transport more goods than the Russian giant.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Power Generator
programme.desc: A three hundred and ninety ton giant on a daring journey: A team of German heavy-lift-specialists have to transport a generator from a disused coal plant to its new operation site 120 kilometers away.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Live to Tell: Hunting Humans
programme.desc: In July 2007, Shea McDonough returned home and left the back door open for her brother, not knowing he wasn’t coming home for the night. Hours later, when her father went to her room to check on her, he saw a masked man standing over her with a knife.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Every Picture Tells A Story
programme.desc: On February 15, 2009, Cathy McNaughton was stabbed to death in her home in Sharpsburg, Georgia. The day had started with her husband Alec serving her breakfast in bed.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Death Wish
programme.desc: A report surrounding the July 2009 death of Jeffrey Locker, whose body was found slumped over the steering wheel of his car in Harlem, New York. When authorities tracked Locker’s ATM card to Kenneth Minor, Minor said Locker had begged Minor to kill him.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Sweetheart Murders
programme.desc: The story of sweethearts Sabrina Gonsalves and John Riggins who were brutally murdered in Davis, California, in 1980. Initially, police suspected Gerald Gallego, but he was in jail at the time of the murders.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Year We Disappeared

programme.title: Christophers Movie Matinee
programme.desc: When movie cameras were put in the hands of a few young people, they made this film about themselves and their world. The film is revealing in what it shows of a dissenting generation and its rationale.

programme.title: Notmans World
programme.desc: William Notman was a man of rare talent. Photography was still in its infancy when he opened his first studio--in Montréal--in the late 1850s. He rapidly turned his art, and a budding technology, into a highly successful business.

programme.title: Totem Talk
programme.desc: Urban Indigenous teens embark on a surreal journey guided by a magical raven, encountering animated totem pole characters and exploring Northwest First Nation culture's significance. Featuring insights from artist J. Bradley Hunt.

programme.title: Firewords Louky Bersianik Jovette Marchessault Nicole Brossa
programme.desc: Firewords offers an intimate glimpse of three respected, controversial Québec writers.Louky Bersianik, Jovette Marchessault and Nicole Brossard have contributed greatly to the creation of a distinctive women's literature.

programme.title: Ladies And Gentlemen Mr Leonard Cohen
programme.desc: Produced in 1965, this is an informal portrait of the Montreal poet, novelist and songwriter, Leonard Cohen. He is seen reading his poetry to a rapt audience and also alone, or relaxing with family and friends.

programme.title: To A Safer Place
programme.desc: To a Safer Place" follows Shirley Turcotte's journey as an incest survivor. Returning to her past, she confronts family violence with courage. Her story inspires survivors to find healing and dignity through frank disclosures.

programme.title: Forgotten Warriors
programme.desc: Although they could not be conscripted, when World War II was declared, thousands of Indigenous Canadian men and women enlisted and fought alongside their non-Indigenous countrymen. They fought for freedom while being denied their own.

programme.title: The Town Mouse And The Country Mouse
programme.desc: Evelyn Lambart's animation style shines in this short film adapting an Aesop fable. It contrasts two mice's lifestyles, advocating for simplicity and peace over luxury amid danger.

programme.title: Neighbours Voisins
programme.desc: Two neighbours live side by side in harmony until a flower grows on the dividing line between their properties. Who does it belong to? The argument that follows ends up with both neighbours in their graves. The most famous of Norman McLaren’s films.

programme.title: Sun Wind And Wood
programme.desc: People combat high energy costs with inventive solar, wind, and wood solutions. This film showcases experiments like the Ark, a bio-shelter sustaining a family with housing, heat, food, and electricity using natural systems.

programme.title: Hands Of History
programme.desc: In this acclaimed 1994 documentary, Loretta Todd, a leading figure in Indigenous cinema in Canada, profiles four contemporary female artists.The film is a moving testimony to the vital role Indigenous women play in nurturing Indigenous cultures.

programme.title: Safe Distance, A
programme.desc: A Safe Distance examines the services needed by and available to battered women. The film looks at some innovative approaches to providing services and accommodation for battered women in rural, northern, and Native communities.

programme.title: Challenger An Industrial Romance
programme.desc: Follows the development of Canadair's super-executive jet. The film captures the spirit of the Canadian air transport industry and its attempt to compete with the American leaders in the industry.

programme.title: The Man Who Stole Dreams
programme.desc: This enchanting and magical animation film, an ode to our dreams during the night, celebrates the creative imagination, uniqueness, and the human spirit. The plot involves a man who steals the dreams of villagers, the tries to sell them back to the them.

programme.title: Its Just Better
programme.desc: At the farmhouse on Cape Breton Island where Shawn Peter Dwyer, age ten, lives with his mother and nine brothers and sisters, a team effort keeps the family functioning.

programme.title: The Way It Is
programme.desc: The Way It Is" explores divorce's effects on a family, centered on twelve-year-old Helen. Her journey to acceptance offers insights for all ages, suitable for family-life courses, single-parent groups, and counseling.

programme.title: Boys Will Be Men
programme.desc: This film takes an inside look at the world of juvenile delinquency. We are shown the tough existence on the streets of Montréal, but it could be any city in North America. Some boys as young as ten years of age talk about their lives of crime.

programme.title: Sea Dream
programme.desc: Children, like adults, have days that go wrong. This film shows how one little girl overcomes the day's frustrations by diving into an underwater fantasy where she spends time with her friend, the lady octopus.

programme.title: If You Love This Planet
programme.desc: This film records a lecture given to students by outspoken nuclear critic, Dr. Helen Caldicott, president of Physicians for Social Responsibility in the United States. Her message is clear: disarmament cannot be postponed.

programme.title: The Story Of Peter And The Potter
programme.desc: When Peter accidentally breaks a glass bowl intended as a birthday gift for his mother, Mr. and Mrs. Deichmann and their daughter Anneke, all artisans in clay, come to the rescue and make him one of their designs while Peter watches.

programme.title: Danish Poet, The
programme.desc: Can we trace the chain of events that leads to our own birth? Is our existence just coincidence? The Danish Poet considers these questions as we follow a poet whose creative well has run dry, on a holiday to Norway to meet a famous writer.

programme.title: Waiting
programme.desc: The patient Dinkas of South Sudan endure famine amid civil strife. Aid arrives in Alek, but distribution is delayed to prevent unrest, revealing the stark reality of hunger.

programme.title: Chateau De Sable / The Sand Castle
programme.desc: A fable of great humour and appeal, The Sand Castle is the story of the Sandman and the creatures he sculpts out of sand. Under his direction, they build a castle and celebrate the completion of their new home, only to be interrupted by an uninvited guest

programme.title: The Big Swim
programme.desc: This film shows Canada's top swimmers in training for the 1964 Olympic Games. Under the critical eye of coach Ed Healy, they practise long hours in gymnasium and pool to build strength and stamina.

programme.title: Chaque Enfant
programme.desc: This is the story of a baby who appears mysteriously on the doorstep of a busy executive, and who is subsequently bounced from household to household down the block. Nobody in the community is interested in caring for the baby without a name.

programme.title: Toward Intimacy
programme.desc: Toward Intimacy" celebrates the rights of women with disabilities to pursue intimate relationships. This one-hour film features personal stories from four Canadian women, addressing sexuality, self-esteem, stereotypes, and parenting.

programme.title: Return To Vimy
programme.desc: Colourized archive footage that takes us back in time to revisit the daily lives of the soldiers of the Canadian Corps, witnessing the long and detailed preparation that lead to this legendary battle.

programme.title: Alphee Of The Stars
programme.desc: Alphée of the Stars puts the spotlight on a most unusual girl. With patience and tenderness, a father – who believes in schools that embrace diversity and do not discriminate – challenges our assumptions and reveals an unknown world.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Mistelzweige küsst man nicht
programme.desc: Zu Weihnachten kehrt Darcy nach Hause zurück und läuft dort ihrem Highschool-Erzfeind Luke über den Weg. Als beide bei der Vorbereitung einer weihnachtlichen Wohltätigkeitsgala helfen, erkennen sie, dass ihre bisherige Abneigung womöglich voreilig war.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston

programme.desc: Jack Campbell é um solteiro convicto que há 13 anos desistiu de um grande amor para se tornar um empresário bem sucedido. Até que na véspera do Natal ele passa por uma experiência traumática e, ao acordar, vê-se numa nova vida.

programme.title: De Repente o Amor Acontece
programme.desc: Sadie, uma executiva de marketing de sucesso, é filha dos donos de uma tradicional loja de chocolates. Ao decidir passar o Natal com a família, descobre que seus pais planejam vender a loja, colocando em risco seu sonho de um dia herdá-la.

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Só Pode Ser Amor
programme.desc: Durante a temporada de Natal, três irmãs terão que decidir o que fazer com sua vida romântica quando partem para encontrar a família para as festas e seus respectivos pares surgem na cidade para tentar uma segunda chance.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: A Viagem de Joy
programme.desc: O desejo de Natal de uma estudante tímida de liceu torna-se realidade, só que não é exatamente tão maravilhoso como ela esperava.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Lareira Festiva
programme.desc: Cozy up to the special edition fireplace, just in time for the Holidays. The soft crackling of burning wood will turn your home into a calming retreat.

programme.title: Músicas de Natal
programme.desc: Crie uma atmosfera calorosa de férias em sua casa com as imagens e sons do Natal, filmados em alta definição.

programme.title: La Navidad de mi Mejor Amigo
programme.desc: Durante una visita a su pueblo natal, una mujer se entera de que su ex novio tiene una nueva relación. Entonces, le pide a su mejor amigo que se haga pasar por su novio.

programme.title: Un Intruso En Navidad
programme.desc: Izzy, de 9 años, se enfrenta a unos secuestradores cuando sus padres llegan tarde el último día antes de las vacaciones de Navidad.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Agujetas para navidad
programme.desc: Cuando el padre de Jennifer la fuerza a ser voluntaria en un refugio para enseñarle compasión y responsabilidad, ella crea un impensado lazo con el equipo, y un pequeño y especial invitado que la hará comprender el verdadero significado de la Navidad.

programme.title: Pan Cielo
programme.desc: Lilli y Annibale, una pareja de sin techo, encuentran un bebé en un contenedor. Llevan al bebé al hospital infantil más cercano, pero una vez allí viven una situación surrealista: ninguno de los médicos o enfermeras puede ver al niño.

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.title: La Navidad de mi Mejor Amigo
programme.desc: Durante una visita a su pueblo natal, una mujer se entera de que su ex novio tiene una nueva relación. Entonces, le pide a su mejor amigo que se haga pasar por su novio.

programme.title: Un Intruso En Navidad
programme.desc: Izzy, de 9 años, se enfrenta a unos secuestradores cuando sus padres llegan tarde el último día antes de las vacaciones de Navidad.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Agujetas para navidad
programme.desc: Cuando el padre de Jennifer la fuerza a ser voluntaria en un refugio para enseñarle compasión y responsabilidad, ella crea un impensado lazo con el equipo, y un pequeño y especial invitado que la hará comprender el verdadero significado de la Navidad.

programme.title: Pan Cielo
programme.desc: Lilli y Annibale, una pareja de sin techo, encuentran un bebé en un contenedor. Llevan al bebé al hospital infantil más cercano, pero una vez allí viven una situación surrealista: ninguno de los médicos o enfermeras puede ver al niño.

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.title: La Navidad de mi Mejor Amigo
programme.desc: Durante una visita a su pueblo natal, una mujer se entera de que su ex novio tiene una nueva relación. Entonces, le pide a su mejor amigo que se haga pasar por su novio.

programme.title: Un Intruso En Navidad
programme.desc: Izzy, de 9 años, se enfrenta a unos secuestradores cuando sus padres llegan tarde el último día antes de las vacaciones de Navidad.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Agujetas para navidad
programme.desc: Cuando el padre de Jennifer la fuerza a ser voluntaria en un refugio para enseñarle compasión y responsabilidad, ella crea un impensado lazo con el equipo, y un pequeño y especial invitado que la hará comprender el verdadero significado de la Navidad.

programme.title: Pan Cielo
programme.desc: Lilli y Annibale, una pareja de sin techo, encuentran un bebé en un contenedor. Llevan al bebé al hospital infantil más cercano, pero una vez allí viven una situación surrealista: ninguno de los médicos o enfermeras puede ver al niño.

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.desc: Die 15. größte Insel der Welt, aber die größte der Philippinen. Ein Land der Kontraste Von der Zersiedelung der Hauptstadt Manila bis hin zu riesigen versteckten Wäldern, den artenreichsten Riffen der Welt und einem Dutzend aktiver Vulkane, die die Skyline dominieren. Nigel trifft auf die außergewöhnlichen Kreaturen, die in diesen Landschaften leben.

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Palawan, die westlichste Insel des Archipels, ist als letzte Grenze bekannt. Nigel wird seine alten Regenwälder, unberührten Küsten, Korallenriffe und unglaublichen unterirdischen Schätze erkunden.

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Die verstreuten Inseln Mindanao (die zweitgrößte der Philippinen), Bohol und Cebu beherbergen eine bizarre Vielfalt an Lebewesen und atemberaubende Landschaften. Nigel stellt uns Bohols weltberühmte Chocolate Hills vor, seltsame Hügel aus aufgelösten Korallen, die etwa 45 Millionen Jahre alt sind, und den legendären Mount Apo, wo der seltenste Adler der Welt sein Comeback feiert.

programme.title: Pinguine unter der Sonne Afrikas
programme.desc: In der Algoa Bay im Süden des afrikanischen Kontinents liegen die Brutinseln vieler Brillenpinguin-Kolonien. Sie sind die einzigen Pinguine, die unter der afrikanischen Sonne leben.

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Diese Folge spürt rund um den Globus einige unserer nächsten Verwandten auf. Primaten jeder Größe haben ihren Auftritt, vom Zwergseidenäffchen im Amazonasbecken bis hin zum imposanten Mandrill in den Tropen Afrikas. Hier dient Körperpflege der Friedensstiftung, Gähnen ist ein Zeichen der Aggression, und manche Affen heben in ihren Backentaschen einen Snack für später auf.

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Ob watschelnd, hüpfend oder schwimmend, die 18 Vertreter der allseits beliebten Pinguinfamilie sind skurril und doch vornehm anzusehen. Die torpedoförmigen, flugunfähigen Seevögel im schwarz-weißen Frack sind treu ergebene Partner, aufopfernde Eltern und schlaue Jäger. Es ist ein spektakulärer Anblick, wenn sie sich zu Hunderttausenden in Kolonien zusammenfinden

programme.title: China, Im Reich der Musuo-Frauen
programme.desc: Am Lugu See im Südwesten Chinas lebt das Volk der Mosuo. Bei ihnen bestimmen die Frauen über alles, was wichtig ist: Sie tragen die Verantwortung für die Familie, wählen ihre Liebhaber, vererben Namen und Besitz an die Töchter. Auch die Schutzgöttin der Mosuo ist weiblich: Aus Berggöttin Gemus Tränen, so die Legende, entstand der See, der das Gebiet der Mosuo begrenzt. Die 29-jährige Lamu Mian Zhe ist am See aufgewachsen. Sie wird bald die Führung der Familie von ihrer Mutter übernehmen.

programme.title: Bolivien -? Lebensader Todesstraße
programme.desc: Bolivien ist das Land mit den größten Höhenunterschieden Südamerikas. Zwischen dem Hochland der Anden im Westen und dem Quellgebiet des Amazonas im Osten fällt die Landschaft um 4.000 Meter ab. Mittendrin liegen die steilen Täler und Hänge der Yungas - mit den gefährlichsten Straßen der Welt. Allen voran die Carretera de la Muerte?: die Todesstraße!

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: An Indiens Schulen bekommen täglich Millionen Schüler ein kostenloses Mittagessen. Die Mahlzeiten müssen in wenigen Stunden zubereitet und an die öffentlichen Schulen der Umgebung ausgeliefert werden - trotz HighTech- Küchen und ausgeklügelter Logistik eine große Herausforderung.Neun Tonnen Gemüse, 15 Tonnen Reis und Gewürze, die nicht in Gramm sondern in Kilogramm den Gerichten beigefügt werden - das ist Alltag in der hochmodernen Großküche von Hubli im Südwesten Indiens, wo jeden Morgen 50 Mitarbeiter Mittagessen für 180.000 Schüler der Region zubereiten. Insgesamt versorgt die Freiwilligen-Organisation mehrere Millionen Schüler im ganzen Land. Wir haben den indischen Köchen in die Töpfe und ihren kleinen Kunden auf den Teller geschaut.

programme.title: Guano
programme.desc: Millionen Seevögel nisten und brüten auf den Inseln an der Pazifikküste Perus. Der Kot der Tiere ist reich an Nährstoffen und daher überaus wertvoll: Als Guano-Dünger wird er in die ganze Welt exportiert. Abgebaut wird die Substanz noch heute per Hand - wie schon vor Jahrhunderten von den Inka. Nur die stärksten Männer ertragen die harte Arbeit und monatelange Isolation auf den unbewohnten Inseln. Der bestialische Gestank des Vogelkots setzt ihnen zu, der Staub verätzt ihre Lungen. Die körperlichen Anstrengungen sind unter diesen extremen Bedingungen noch schwerer zu ertragen. Wir haben die Guano-Arbeiter begleitet - entstanden ist ein Portrait über Perus Inseln der Qualen.

programme.title: In den Smaragdbergen von Bahia
programme.desc: Acht Uhr morgens, es ist schon heiß in Salvador da Bahia, doch in die vornehme Altstadtvilla weht ein frischer Wind vom Meer. Hier residiert der gebürtige Schweizer Daniel Kläy. Er kam vor 20 Jahren nur mit einer Gitarre nach Brasilien. Heute ist er einer der angesehensten Juwelenhändler. Seine Liebe gilt vor allem den Smaragden, doch die Jagd nach dem unergründlich moosgrünen Juwel wird immer schwieriger. Vor kurzem wurde eine -von Daniel Kläys Minen überraschend von der Regierung geschlossen. Planet Weltweit hat einen besonderen Einblick in die Geheimnisse von Brasiliens Smaragdgeschäft bekommen.Der Karneval steht vor der Tür, aber so richtig nach Feiern ist Daniel Kläy nicht zumute. Seine Mine ist von der Regierung geschlossen worden.

programme.title: Die neuen Nomaden von Kirgisistan
programme.desc: Bachit ist ein cleverer Hirte. Längst hat der 40-jährige Kirgise begriffen, dass sich etwas Entscheidendes verändert in seiner Heimat, dem an der Grenze zu China gelegenen Tien Shan Gebirge: Die bis zu 7000 Meter hohen Gipfel tauen rasant im Vergleich zu früheren Jahrzehnten. Eine Folge der Klimaerwärmung, mit noch ungeahnten globalen Auswirkungen. Bachit hat sich auf die neue Situation eingestellt: Seit mehreren Jahren treibt er im Mai seine riesige Viehherde aus dem Dorf auf eine 3000 Meter hohe Sommeralm - und ist dabei zunehmend Schwierigkeiten ausgesetzt. Planet Weltweit begleitet die kirgisische Nomadenfamilie und ihre 600 Tiere auf dem abenteuerlichen Treck durch Schluchten und reißende Gebirgsströme.

programme.title: Die Feuerflieger von Valencia
programme.desc: "Die Feuerflieger von Valencia"Ein Film von Jost Listemann und Christian SchaafJedes Jahr verliert Spanien mehrere zehntausend Hektar Wald durch Feuer. Besonders in den heißen Sommermonaten wüten unzählige Feuer das ausgetrocknete Land und vernichten ganze Regionen. Gelingt es nicht, die Feuer stoppen, wird in 50 Jahren die Hälfte der spanischen Wälder für immer verloren sein. Um diese Entwicklung aufzuhalten, bekämpft eine Feuerpatrouille aus Hubschraubern und Löschflugzeugen Brände bereits aus der Luft. Planet Weltweit hat die Männer dieser Staffel besucht und sie einen Sommer lang bei ihren Einsätzen begleitet.

programme.title: Make-up und Motorenöl
programme.desc: Wer im Kaffeeanbaugebiet Kolumbiens etwas auf sich hält, fährt einen Willys?. Der legendäre und robuste Geländewagen aus den USA wurde bekannt als das Auto, das den zweiten Weltkrieg gewann.? Seit den 1950iger Jahren ist der Vater aller Jeeps auch in Kolumbien im Einsatz, denn das robuste Fahrzeug ist wie geschaffen für das bergige Gelände. Bis zu 50 Prozent Gefälle müssen die Willys bewältigen. Etliche Fincas sind nur über halsbrecherische, unbefestigte Pisten erreichbar. Im Macho-Land Kolumbien saßen bislang nur Männer am Lenkrad der Geländewagen. Johana Londo?o setzt dieser Tradition ein Ende. Planet Weltweit ist unterwegs mit Kolumbiens einziger Willys-Fahrerin.

programme.title: Die Krieger vom Dach der Welt
programme.desc: Nepal - Die Krieger vom Dach der Welt?Ein Film von Karl Alexander WeckDas Himalaja-Massiv von Nepal ist die Heimat der wohl gefürchtetsten Krieger der Welt: der Gurkhas. Ihr hartes Leben auf dem Dach der Welt macht sie zu zähen und mutigen Persönlichkeiten. Seit Generationen stehen sie im Dienst der britischen Armee. Für die heranwachsende Jugend aus den abgelegenen Bergdörfern ist ein Leben als Soldat auch heute noch ein heiß begehrtes Lebensziel. Der Sold auf europäischem Niveau ermöglicht es den Gurkhas, ihre Familien finanziell zu unterstützen und damit auch deren Ansehen zu erhöhen. Planet Weltweit begleitet einen so genannten Galla Wallah - einen Gurkha-Scout - auf seiner Suche nach neuen Gurkha-Kämpfern. Der pensionierte Ex-Gurkha ist mit der Auswahl der aussichtsreichsten Bewerber betraut. Sein Weg führt ihn in entlegene Bergdörfer, quer durch die atemberaubende Landschaft des Himalajas. Der junge Santosh aus dem Bergdorf Tangting hat einen Traum: Er möchte als Gurkha in den Militärdienst der britischen Armee aufgenommen werden. Ein solcher Posten ist für die in Armut lebenden Nepalis in den entlegenen Provinzen wie ein Lottogewinn: Ca. 1.500 Euro Monatssold bedeuten hier ein sorgenfreies Leben für die ganze Familie. programme.title: Benny Goodman, Scott Hamilton, John Bunch & Phil Flanigan
programme.sub-title: Benny Goodman Septet - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1982, legendary jazz clarinettist Benny Goodman performed at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague with his septet. The “King of Swing” revisited the atmosphere of the 1930s, when jazz enjoyed tremendous popularity.

programme.title: Kenny Barron
programme.desc: Pianist Kenny Barron's June 27, 2019 appearance at the Alfa Jazz Festival in Ukraine's Lviv was a celebration of sublime jazz virtuosity. The revered elder statesmen of jazz piano brought his regular working trio of Kiyoshi Kitagawa (bass) and Jonathan Blake (drums), augmented by stellar jazzman Marcus Strickland (tenor saxophone) and young lion Riley Mulherkar (trumpet). Their seamless blend of classic bebop and modern explorations spoke of a deep, emotive connection to each note, captivating the Ukrainian audience with lyrical improvisations during this unforgettable concert.

programme.title: Michael Mossman
programme.sub-title: Munich Philharmonic Hall: Michel Camilo Quintet
programme.desc: Well-known for his exuberant style and intimate familiarity with a vast range of jazz and Latin idioms, Michel Camilo has always had a sixth sense for musical adventure. Camilo was one of the most stimulating jazz pianists to emerge in the mid- to late '80s. His powerful two-handed attack (full of impressive technical skills), his knowledge of both jazz and Afro-Cuban music, and his willingness to constantly take chances turn each of his solos into an adventure. This broadcast was taped during the 1991 Münchner Klaviersommer, when Camilo was playing with his amazing Quintet. He is accompanied by Ned Mann (bass), Cliff Almond (drums), Michel Mossman (trumpet and trombone) and Ralph Bowen (saxophone and flute). Camilo's rise to fame has been swift, and his influences range from jazz musicians like Art Tatum and Keith Jarrett to twentieth-century composers like Debussy and Ravel.

programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Herbie Hancock & The Headhunter
programme.desc: American keyboard player and bandleader Herbie Hancock (1940) achieved success as an incisive, harmonically provocative jazz pianist in the 1960s, then went on to gain wide popularity as a leader of electric jazz-rock groups. One of these, Hancock's band The Headhunters, ushered in a new era of jazz that appealed to a far wider audience, making jazz listeners out of rhythm and blues fans, and vice versa. In 1974, The Headhunters appeared on German television, playing Palm Grease, Sly, Butterfly, Spank-A-Lee, and Chameleon. Hancock (keys) is joined by Bennie Maupin (saxophones), Paul Jackson (electric bass), Mike Clark (drums) and Bill Summer (percussion).

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: Trombone Shorty
programme.sub-title: Troy 'Trombone Shorty' Andrews: Jazz à Vienne
programme.desc: Jazz phenomenon Trombone Shorty dishes out a mix of funk, jazz, hip-hop and soul at this concert at the French festival Jazz à Vienne. Playing with the energy of a rock star, Troy Andrews, a.k.a. ‘Trombone Shorty', pays homage to jazz legends. With his hypnotic performance and boundless energy, Trombone Shorty puts up an unparalleled performance.

programme.sub-title: Ahmad Jamal Trio - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1989, legendary jazz pianist Ahmad Jamal brought his trio to the North Sea Jazz Festival. Accompanied by James Cammack on bass and David Bowler on drums, Jamal showcased his excellence.

programme.title: Kylie Minogue
programme.desc: Two hours of classic Kylie, capturing the energy, grandeur and extravagance of the massively acclaimed Aphrodite: Les Folies tour. Filmed at Kylie's triumphant O2 Arena show in London, this concert film was produced using a lavishly hi-tech multi-camera shoot affording the viewer a spectacular experience from start to finish. The 2-hour show proved to be one of the most elaborate and extravagant productions ever staged by a pop performer, a multi-million dollar visual and musical feast, that delighted critics and fans alike wherever it played. Now Kylie's fans can re-live the experience with this amazing 2-hour document, which includes all of her best-known modern hits- "Can t Get You Out Of My Head", "Spinning Around"- as well as her four Billboard Club smashes from 2010's acclaimed "Aphrodite" album including "All The Lovers" and "Get Outta My Way".

programme.title: Huelgas Ensemble & Paul Van Nevel
programme.desc: Conductor Paul Van Nevel and his Huelgas Ensemble present the ideal Christmas program, consisting of an atmospheric musical selection of 14th to 19th-century compositions. The Huelgas Ensemble, which has emerged as one of Europe's premiere vocal ensembles dedicated to the performance of music from the Middle Ages and the Renaissance, is the ideal candidate for the job, conveying all the mystery and luster a Christmas celebration calls for. Van Nevel organized his varied musical selection in four distinct themes: ‘The Birth in Bethlehem', ‘The Crime of Herodes', ‘The Travel of the Three Kings', and an Epilogue. In 2015, the full program was performed and recorded at the baroque St. Augustine Church currently known as AMUZ in Antwerp, Belgium. ‘The Birth in Bethlehem' opens and closes with pieces by unidentified composers, 'Balaam de quo Vaticinans' and 'A Carol for Christmas Eve' respectively. The core of this section is made up of Jacobus Gallus's 'Myrabile Mysterium' and Jerónimo Luca's 'Este nino que es sol del Aurora'. ‘The Crime of Herodes' opens with 'Hostis Herodes Impie' by an unidentified composer, followed by Jean Mouton's 'Interrogabat Magos Herodes', Giaches De Wert's 'Vox in Rama', and Bertram Luard-Selby's 'A Voice from Ramah was There Sent'. ‘The Travel of the Three Kings Melchior, Caspar and Balthazar' opens with 'Vincti Presepio' (anonymous), followed by Pierre De Manchicourt's 'Reges Terrae', Jan Pieterszoon Sweelinck's 'Ab Oriente', and Peter Cornelius 'Drei Könige Wandern'. Lastly, the Epilogue consists of 'Quae Stella Sole Pulchrior' (anonymous) and António Marques Lésbio's 'Dexen que Ilore mi Niño'.

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. The program continues with a fine selection of Bach's works performed by French lutenist Thomas Dunford. On the program are Suite for lute in G minor, BWV 995 Suite for solo cello in G major (arr. for lute), BWV 1007 and Chaconne from Partita for solo violin in D minor (arr. lute), BWV 1004. This concert was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, in 2017.

programme.title: Rodolfo Mederos, Otros Aires, Teresa Parodi & Café de los Maestros
programme.desc: For the audience in the famous ballroom El Palacio in Buenos Aires, the year 2012 began with tango rhythms and Argentinean folk music. This festive broadcast opens with a tango performance by dance partners Eduardo and Gloria, accompanied by the renowned ensemble Café de los Maestros. Another highlights is a performance by bandoneon player Rodolfo Mederos and his trio. In addition, the concert features a performance by Teresa Parodi, former lead singer of the Astor Piazzolla Band, accompanied by the Fernando Suárez Paz Quintet. Also on the bill is the contemporary electronic tango formation Otros Aires. Founded by Miguel Di Genova in 2003, Otros Aires combines electronic rhythms and traditional tango instruments, such as the bandoneon, piano, and guitar. On the program are compositions by Astor Piazzolla, Pedro Maffia, Pedro Laurenz, Gustavo Mozzi, and many others. Enjoy this concert of music and dance, featuring some of Argentine's tango scene's finest artists!

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Herbert Blomstedt & Lucerne Festival Orchestra
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Piano Concerto No. 1 & Symphony No. 2
programme.desc: At the age of seven, Argentine pianist Martha Argerich made her debut with Ludwig van Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 1 in C major, Op. 15, a piece that would accompany her throughout her career. The celebrated pianist performs this signature piece at the Lucerne Festival with the Lucerne Festival Orchestra under the baton of Swedish conductor Herbert Blomstedt, who makes his festival debut with the orchestra. Beethoven's Symphony No. 2 in D major, Op. 36, is also on the program. This performance was recorded at the Lucerne Culture and Congress Center (KKL), Switzerland, in August 2020.

It has more turtle visitors than humans!

programme.title: China, Im Reich der Musuo-Frauen
programme.desc: Am Lugu See im Südwesten Chinas lebt das Volk der Mosuo. Bei ihnen bestimmen die Frauen über alles, was wichtig ist: Sie tragen die Verantwortung für die Familie, wählen ihre Liebhaber, vererben Namen und Besitz an die Töchter. Auch die Schutzgöttin der Mosuo ist weiblich: Aus Berggöttin Gemus Tränen, so die Legende, entstand der See, der das Gebiet der Mosuo begrenzt. Die 29-jährige Lamu Mian Zhe ist am See aufgewachsen. Sie wird bald die Führung der Familie von ihrer Mutter übernehmen.

programme.title: Bolivien -? Lebensader Todesstraße
programme.desc: Bolivien ist das Land mit den größten Höhenunterschieden Südamerikas. Zwischen dem Hochland der Anden im Westen und dem Quellgebiet des Amazonas im Osten fällt die Landschaft um 4.000 Meter ab. Mittendrin liegen die steilen Täler und Hänge der Yungas - mit den gefährlichsten Straßen der Welt. Allen voran die Carretera de la Muerte?: die Todesstraße!

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: An Indiens Schulen bekommen täglich Millionen Schüler ein kostenloses Mittagessen. Die Mahlzeiten müssen in wenigen Stunden zubereitet und an die öffentlichen Schulen der Umgebung ausgeliefert werden - trotz HighTech- Küchen und ausgeklügelter Logistik eine große Herausforderung.Neun Tonnen Gemüse, 15 Tonnen Reis und Gewürze, die nicht in Gramm sondern in Kilogramm den Gerichten beigefügt werden - das ist Alltag in der hochmodernen Großküche von Hubli im Südwesten Indiens, wo jeden Morgen 50 Mitarbeiter Mittagessen für 180.000 Schüler der Region zubereiten. Insgesamt versorgt die Freiwilligen-Organisation mehrere Millionen Schüler im ganzen Land. Wir haben den indischen Köchen in die Töpfe und ihren kleinen Kunden auf den Teller geschaut.

programme.title: Guano
programme.desc: Millionen Seevögel nisten und brüten auf den Inseln an der Pazifikküste Perus. Der Kot der Tiere ist reich an Nährstoffen und daher überaus wertvoll: Als Guano-Dünger wird er in die ganze Welt exportiert. Abgebaut wird die Substanz noch heute per Hand - wie schon vor Jahrhunderten von den Inka. Nur die stärksten Männer ertragen die harte Arbeit und monatelange Isolation auf den unbewohnten Inseln. Der bestialische Gestank des Vogelkots setzt ihnen zu, der Staub verätzt ihre Lungen. Die körperlichen Anstrengungen sind unter diesen extremen Bedingungen noch schwerer zu ertragen. Wir haben die Guano-Arbeiter begleitet - entstanden ist ein Portrait über Perus Inseln der Qualen.

programme.title: In den Smaragdbergen von Bahia
programme.desc: Acht Uhr morgens, es ist schon heiß in Salvador da Bahia, doch in die vornehme Altstadtvilla weht ein frischer Wind vom Meer. Hier residiert der gebürtige Schweizer Daniel Kläy. Er kam vor 20 Jahren nur mit einer Gitarre nach Brasilien. Heute ist er einer der angesehensten Juwelenhändler. Seine Liebe gilt vor allem den Smaragden, doch die Jagd nach dem unergründlich moosgrünen Juwel wird immer schwieriger. Vor kurzem wurde eine -von Daniel Kläys Minen überraschend von der Regierung geschlossen. Planet Weltweit hat einen besonderen Einblick in die Geheimnisse von Brasiliens Smaragdgeschäft bekommen.Der Karneval steht vor der Tür, aber so richtig nach Feiern ist Daniel Kläy nicht zumute. Seine Mine ist von der Regierung geschlossen worden.

programme.title: Die neuen Nomaden von Kirgisistan
programme.desc: Bachit ist ein cleverer Hirte. Längst hat der 40-jährige Kirgise begriffen, dass sich etwas Entscheidendes verändert in seiner Heimat, dem an der Grenze zu China gelegenen Tien Shan Gebirge: Die bis zu 7000 Meter hohen Gipfel tauen rasant im Vergleich zu früheren Jahrzehnten. Eine Folge der Klimaerwärmung, mit noch ungeahnten globalen Auswirkungen. Bachit hat sich auf die neue Situation eingestellt: Seit mehreren Jahren treibt er im Mai seine riesige Viehherde aus dem Dorf auf eine 3000 Meter hohe Sommeralm - und ist dabei zunehmend Schwierigkeiten ausgesetzt. Planet Weltweit begleitet die kirgisische Nomadenfamilie und ihre 600 Tiere auf dem abenteuerlichen Treck durch Schluchten und reißende Gebirgsströme.

programme.title: Die Feuerflieger von Valencia
programme.desc: "Die Feuerflieger von Valencia"Ein Film von Jost Listemann und Christian SchaafJedes Jahr verliert Spanien mehrere zehntausend Hektar Wald durch Feuer. Besonders in den heißen Sommermonaten wüten unzählige Feuer das ausgetrocknete Land und vernichten ganze Regionen. Gelingt es nicht, die Feuer stoppen, wird in 50 Jahren die Hälfte der spanischen Wälder für immer verloren sein. Um diese Entwicklung aufzuhalten, bekämpft eine Feuerpatrouille aus Hubschraubern und Löschflugzeugen Brände bereits aus der Luft. Planet Weltweit hat die Männer dieser Staffel besucht und sie einen Sommer lang bei ihren Einsätzen begleitet.

programme.title: Make-up und Motorenöl
programme.desc: Wer im Kaffeeanbaugebiet Kolumbiens etwas auf sich hält, fährt einen Willys?. Der legendäre und robuste Geländewagen aus den USA wurde bekannt als das Auto, das den zweiten Weltkrieg gewann.? Seit den 1950iger Jahren ist der Vater aller Jeeps auch in Kolumbien im Einsatz, denn das robuste Fahrzeug ist wie geschaffen für das bergige Gelände. Bis zu 50 Prozent Gefälle müssen die Willys bewältigen. Etliche Fincas sind nur über halsbrecherische, unbefestigte Pisten erreichbar. Im Macho-Land Kolumbien saßen bislang nur Männer am Lenkrad der Geländewagen. Johana Londo?o setzt dieser Tradition ein Ende. Planet Weltweit ist unterwegs mit Kolumbiens einziger Willys-Fahrerin.

programme.title: Die Krieger vom Dach der Welt
programme.desc: Nepal - Die Krieger vom Dach der Welt?Ein Film von Karl Alexander WeckDas Himalaja-Massiv von Nepal ist die Heimat der wohl gefürchtetsten Krieger der Welt: der Gurkhas. Ihr hartes Leben auf dem Dach der Welt macht sie zu zähen und mutigen Persönlichkeiten. Seit Generationen stehen sie im Dienst der britischen Armee. Für die heranwachsende Jugend aus den abgelegenen Bergdörfern ist ein Leben als Soldat auch heute noch ein heiß begehrtes Lebensziel. Der Sold auf europäischem Niveau ermöglicht es den Gurkhas, ihre Familien finanziell zu unterstützen und damit auch deren Ansehen zu erhöhen. Planet Weltweit begleitet einen so genannten Galla Wallah - einen Gurkha-Scout - auf seiner Suche nach neuen Gurkha-Kämpfern. Der pensionierte Ex-Gurkha ist mit der Auswahl der aussichtsreichsten Bewerber betraut. Sein Weg führt ihn in entlegene Bergdörfer, quer durch die atemberaubende Landschaft des Himalajas. Der junge Santosh aus dem Bergdorf Tangting hat einen Traum: Er möchte als Gurkha in den Militärdienst der britischen Armee aufgenommen werden. Ein solcher Posten ist für die in Armut lebenden Nepalis in den entlegenen Provinzen wie ein Lottogewinn: Ca. 1.500 Euro Monatssold bedeuten hier ein sorgenfreies Leben für die ganze Familie. programme.title: Princesa Diana ¿Quién crees que era?
programme.desc: Sabemos cómo termina la historia de la Princesa Diana. Pero, ¿cómo comenzó todo? ¿Quién era Diana antes del palacio, antes de los paparazzi? Detrás de la leyenda moderna que es ‘Diana, Princesa de Gales' se esconden muchas otras historias: en su infancia y en el pasado de su familia, los Spencer. El documental Princess Diana: Who Do You Think She Was? ofrece una exploración profunda de Diana, Princesa de Gales, enfocándose en su trasfondo familiar e histórico. La película no solo destaca la icónica vida pública de Diana, sino que también profundiza en sus raíces dentro de la familia Spencer, proporcionando un contexto más amplio a su historia.

programme.title: Príncipe Harry
programme.desc: Mientras el Príncipe Harry se instala en la vida matrimonial, esta película analiza la formación de un Príncipe Guerrero.

programme.title: Diana
programme.sub-title: La Entrevista Que Sacudio Al Mundo
programme.desc: En 1995, la Princesa Diana rompió protocolos en una impactante entrevista con BBC Panorama. 25 años después, este documental analiza cómo se orquestó la exclusiva del siglo, su impacto en la sociedad moderna y ofrece nuevas perspectivas sobre el retrato psicológico de Diana, quien creyó en un cuento de hadas y se perdió en las realidades de su matrimonio. Descubre la verdad detrás de este evento icónico.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: El Rey y su hermana, la Princesa Cristina, comparten sus recuerdos de infancia en el palacio. "En realidad no era un entorno agradable para vivir, más bien parecía un hotel", recuerda el Rey al describir las habitaciones donde él y sus hermanas crecieron en el ala sur del palacio. La Princesa Heredera Victoria nos muestra objetos de valor incalculable en sus habitaciones favoritas "Es un patrimonio cultural fantástico y es impresionante que se conserven estos ambientes, teniendo en cuenta lo antiguos que son. Es un tesoro extraordinario y accesible que nos pertenece a todos", afirma. Los espectadores también tienen la oportunidad de adentrarse entre bastidores antes de una visita de Estado, escuchar historias de fantasmas reales, así como a historiadores, expertos y artesanos que nos ofrecen un retrato único de un tesoro nacional: nuestro Palacio Real.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: Nos subimos a un andamio para averiguar más cosas sobre la renovación de la fachada y llegar al fondo de la cuestión de si el viejo castillo está embrujado. Síganos por los salones dorados y las oscuras bóvedas de los sótanos. El Palacio Real de Estocolmo tiene más de mil habitaciones y cientos de años de historia real. El Rey y su hermana, la princesa Cristina, nos cuentan cómo fue crecer en el palacio. La Princesa Victoria muestra objetos de valor incalculable.

programme.desc: 먹은 예로부터 선비의 친구 문방사우(먹, 종이, 붓, 벼루) 중 하나로 우리의 뛰어난 기록문화유산들을 만드는 중요한 소재였습니다. 소나무를 태워 만든 연기 속에서 얻은 그을음에 아교를 넣어 먹 반죽을 만들고, 형틀에 넣어 먹을 제조하는 송연먹을 제작하는 과정을 함께 감상해봅시다. (한상묵 / 전통 먹장 숙련기술자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 혼을 담은 붓. 필장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널필장은 문방사우(文房四友)의 하나인 붓을 만드는 장인입니다. 붓은 털의 품질이 가장 중요하며 붓끝이 뾰족해야 하고 가지런해야 하며, 털 윗부분이 끈으로 잘 묶여서 둥근 것, 오래 써도 힘이 있어 한 획을 긋고 난 뒤에 붓털이 다시 일어나야 합니다. 수천번의 손길을 거쳐야 완성되는 전통 붓 제작과정을 함께 감상해 보시죠. (유필무 / 충북무형문화재 필장 보유자)

programme.title: [창덕궁 봄꽃 개화 현장] 봄꽃의 향연, 창덕궁 나들이
programme.desc: 창덕궁은 태종 때 건립된 조선왕조의 왕궁으로, 처음에는 경복궁의 이궁으로 지어졌지만 경복궁보다 더욱 오래 법궁의 역할을 해왔습니다. 특히 창덕궁 후원은 한국의 유일한 궁궐후원이라는 점에서 그 가치가 매우 높지요. 한국의 대표적인 정원인 창덕궁이 봄을 맞이하는 아름다운 모습을 감상해보세요! ※ 창덕궁 (사적 제122호, 1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 숲길로 이어진 어머니와 아들, 태릉과 강릉
programme.desc: 서울의 태릉은 조선 제11대 왕 중종의 제2계비인 문정왕후가, 강릉은 조선 제13대 왕 명종과 명종비 인순왕후가 잠들어있는 곳입니다. 두 능은 연결되어있어 태릉에서 호젓한 숲길을 따라 30분 정도 걸으면 강릉까지 한번에 만날 수 있답니다. ※ 서울 태릉과 강릉 (사적 제201호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.1
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: 산사를 듣다. 해남 대흥사
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널대흥사는 해남의 명산인 두륜산도립공원에 위치하며, 명승들의 발자취가 남아있는 곳으로 유명합니다. 특히 승병 서산대사가 사용하던 의발이 모셔져 있고, 대웅보전에는 동국진체를 완성한 원교 이광사가 쓴 편액, 서산대사와 다도사상을 정립한 초의선사 등이 남아있어요. ※ 대흥사 (사적 제 508호) / 산사, 한국의 산지승원 (2018년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: Benny Goodman, Scott Hamilton, John Bunch & Phil Flanigan
programme.sub-title: Benny Goodman Septet - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1982, legendary jazz clarinettist Benny Goodman performed at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague with his septet. The “King of Swing” revisited the atmosphere of the 1930s, when jazz enjoyed tremendous popularity.

programme.title: Kenny Barron
programme.desc: Pianist Kenny Barron's June 27, 2019 appearance at the Alfa Jazz Festival in Ukraine's Lviv was a celebration of sublime jazz virtuosity. The revered elder statesmen of jazz piano brought his regular working trio of Kiyoshi Kitagawa (bass) and Jonathan Blake (drums), augmented by stellar jazzman Marcus Strickland (tenor saxophone) and young lion Riley Mulherkar (trumpet). Their seamless blend of classic bebop and modern explorations spoke of a deep, emotive connection to each note, captivating the Ukrainian audience with lyrical improvisations during this unforgettable concert.

programme.title: Michael Mossman
programme.sub-title: Munich Philharmonic Hall: Michel Camilo Quintet
programme.desc: Well-known for his exuberant style and intimate familiarity with a vast range of jazz and Latin idioms, Michel Camilo has always had a sixth sense for musical adventure. Camilo was one of the most stimulating jazz pianists to emerge in the mid- to late '80s. His powerful two-handed attack (full of impressive technical skills), his knowledge of both jazz and Afro-Cuban music, and his willingness to constantly take chances turn each of his solos into an adventure. This broadcast was taped during the 1991 Münchner Klaviersommer, when Camilo was playing with his amazing Quintet. He is accompanied by Ned Mann (bass), Cliff Almond (drums), Michel Mossman (trumpet and trombone) and Ralph Bowen (saxophone and flute). Camilo's rise to fame has been swift, and his influences range from jazz musicians like Art Tatum and Keith Jarrett to twentieth-century composers like Debussy and Ravel.

programme.title: Herbie Hancock & The Headhunter
programme.desc: American keyboard player and bandleader Herbie Hancock (1940) achieved success as an incisive, harmonically provocative jazz pianist in the 1960s, then went on to gain wide popularity as a leader of electric jazz-rock groups. One of these, Hancock's band The Headhunters, ushered in a new era of jazz that appealed to a far wider audience, making jazz listeners out of rhythm and blues fans, and vice versa. In 1974, The Headhunters appeared on German television, playing Palm Grease, Sly, Butterfly, Spank-A-Lee, and Chameleon. Hancock (keys) is joined by Bennie Maupin (saxophones), Paul Jackson (electric bass), Mike Clark (drums) and Bill Summer (percussion).

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

Playing with the energy of a rock star, Troy Andrews, a.k.a. ‘Trombone Shorty', pays homage to jazz legends. With his hypnotic performance and boundless energy, Trombone Shorty puts up an unparalleled performance.

programme.title: Kylie Minogue
programme.desc: Two hours of classic Kylie, capturing the energy, grandeur and extravagance of the massively acclaimed Aphrodite: Les Folies tour. Filmed at Kylie's triumphant O2 Arena show in London, this concert film was produced using a lavishly hi-tech multi-camera shoot affording the viewer a spectacular experience from start to finish. The 2-hour show proved to be one of the most elaborate and extravagant productions ever staged by a pop performer, a multi-million dollar visual and musical feast, that delighted critics and fans alike wherever it played. Now Kylie's fans can re-live the experience with this amazing 2-hour document, which includes all of her best-known modern hits- "Can t Get You Out Of My Head", "Spinning Around"- as well as her four Billboard Club smashes from 2010's acclaimed "Aphrodite" album including "All The Lovers" and "Get Outta My Way".

programme.title: Huelgas Ensemble & Paul Van Nevel
programme.desc: Conductor Paul Van Nevel and his Huelgas Ensemble present the ideal Christmas program, consisting of an atmospheric musical selection of 14th to 19th-century compositions. The Huelgas Ensemble, which has emerged as one of Europe's premiere vocal ensembles dedicated to the performance of music from the Middle Ages and the Renaissance, is the ideal candidate for the job, conveying all the mystery and luster a Christmas celebration calls for. Van Nevel organized his varied musical selection in four distinct themes: ‘The Birth in Bethlehem', ‘The Crime of Herodes', ‘The Travel of the Three Kings', and an Epilogue. In 2015, the full program was performed and recorded at the baroque St. Augustine Church currently known as AMUZ in Antwerp, Belgium. ‘The Birth in Bethlehem' opens and closes with pieces by unidentified composers, 'Balaam de quo Vaticinans' and 'A Carol for Christmas Eve' respectively. The core of this section is made up of Jacobus Gallus's 'Myrabile Mysterium' and Jerónimo Luca's 'Este nino que es sol del Aurora'. ‘The Crime of Herodes' opens with 'Hostis Herodes Impie' by an unidentified composer, followed by Jean Mouton's 'Interrogabat Magos Herodes', Giaches De Wert's 'Vox in Rama', and Bertram Luard-Selby's 'A Voice from Ramah was There Sent'. ‘The Travel of the Three Kings Melchior, Caspar and Balthazar' opens with 'Vincti Presepio' (anonymous), followed by Pierre De Manchicourt's 'Reges Terrae', Jan Pieterszoon Sweelinck's 'Ab Oriente', and Peter Cornelius 'Drei Könige Wandern'. Lastly, the Epilogue consists of 'Quae Stella Sole Pulchrior' (anonymous) and António Marques Lésbio's 'Dexen que Ilore mi Niño'.

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. The program continues with a fine selection of Bach's works performed by French lutenist Thomas Dunford. On the program are Suite for lute in G minor, BWV 995 Suite for solo cello in G major (arr. for lute), BWV 1007 and Chaconne from Partita for solo violin in D minor (arr. lute), BWV 1004. This concert was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, in 2017.

programme.title: Rodolfo Mederos, Otros Aires, Teresa Parodi & Café de los Maestros
programme.desc: For the audience in the famous ballroom El Palacio in Buenos Aires, the year 2012 began with tango rhythms and Argentinean folk music. This festive broadcast opens with a tango performance by dance partners Eduardo and Gloria, accompanied by the renowned ensemble Café de los Maestros. Another highlights is a performance by bandoneon player Rodolfo Mederos and his trio. In addition, the concert features a performance by Teresa Parodi, former lead singer of the Astor Piazzolla Band, accompanied by the Fernando Suárez Paz Quintet. Also on the bill is the contemporary electronic tango formation Otros Aires. Founded by Miguel Di Genova in 2003, Otros Aires combines electronic rhythms and traditional tango instruments, such as the bandoneon, piano, and guitar. On the program are compositions by Astor Piazzolla, Pedro Maffia, Pedro Laurenz, Gustavo Mozzi, and many others. Enjoy this concert of music and dance, featuring some of Argentine's tango scene's finest artists!

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Herbert Blomstedt & Lucerne Festival Orchestra
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Piano Concerto No. 1 & Symphony No. 2
programme.desc: At the age of seven, Argentine pianist Martha Argerich made her debut with Ludwig van Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 1 in C major, Op. 15, a piece that would accompany her throughout her career. The celebrated pianist performs this signature piece at the Lucerne Festival with the Lucerne Festival Orchestra under the baton of Swedish conductor Herbert Blomstedt, who makes his festival debut with the orchestra. Beethoven's Symphony No. 2 in D major, Op. 36, is also on the program. This performance was recorded at the Lucerne Culture and Congress Center (KKL), Switzerland, in August 2020.

programme.title: A Day in Paradise 1
programme.desc: A graciously flowing four hour long pure nature relaxation experience, "A Day In Paradise" immerses viewers in the sights and sounds of one of the world's most pure and picturesque tropical islands - for an entire day from sunrise, to sunset. Filmed in 2013 by David Huting, the tiny island is hidden off of the northeastern coast of the outer Fiji Islands (near Taveuni), and boasts a perfect white sandy beach, groves of palm trees, and a majestic lagoon that shelters the island from all sides. It has more turtle visitors than humans!
